<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5142635" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5142635" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5142635/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="251" startId="4.[136,229,1929,1951]" targetBox="[151,1435,190,1904]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1452,1929,1987]" pageId="4" pageNumber="251">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,252,1929,1951]" pageId="4" pageNumber="251">FIGURE 4.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[257,523,1929,1950]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="251">
<taxonomicName box="[257,519,1929,1950]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Echeveria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="4" pageNumber="251" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cerrograndensis">Echeveria cerrograndensis</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
A–B. Flower variability. C. Dissected flower showing corolla, one sepal, pistils, stamens and dark red nectaries at the base of the ovary. D–F. Panicle variability. Photographs A–D and F by Antonio Vázquez; E by Gregorio Nieves.
