<paragraph blockId="5.[136,1452,158,761]" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">
Rupicolous perennial rosette; stem single, erect to decumbent, 
<quantity box="[834,916,158,185]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="252" unit="cm" value="3.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="2.0">2–5 cm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity box="[986,1061,158,185]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="5" pageNumber="252" unit="cm" value="1.5">1.5 cm</quantity>
diam., pale brown with darker leaf scars (
<figureCitation box="[208,308,194,220]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[136,229,2032,2054]" captionTargetBox="[186,1400,436,2022]" captionTargetId="figure-158@2.[186,1400,436,2022]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Echeveria cerrograndensis. Habit variability. Photographs A and B by Gregorio Nieves; C by Rodolfo Sánchez; D by Antonio Vázquez." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5142631" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5142631/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">Figure 2</figureCitation>
). Rosettes 
<quantity box="[433,531,194,221]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.5" metricValueMax="11.0" metricValueMin="8.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="252" unit="cm" value="9.5" valueMax="11.0" valueMin="8.0">8–11 cm</quantity>
in diam., lax, closed in winter (
<figureCitation box="[896,995,194,220]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[136,229,1940,1962]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,190,1915]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[151,1435,190,1915]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Echeveria cerrograndensis. Rosette variability. Photographs A and B by Rodolfo Sánchez; C by Gregorio Nieves; and D by Antonio Vázquez." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5142633" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5142633/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">Figure 3</figureCitation>
). Leaves (3–)4–6 
<emphasis box="[1203,1222,195,220]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">×</emphasis>
<quantity box="[1230,1359,194,221]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" metricValueMax="3.5" metricValueMin="2.5" pageId="5" pageNumber="252" unit="cm" value="3.0" valueMax="3.5" valueMin="2.5">2.5–3.5 cm</quantity>
, basally 
<quantity box="[136,264,230,257]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.35" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="5" pageNumber="252" unit="cm" value="1.35" valueMax="1.5" valueMin="1.2">1.2–1.5 cm</quantity>
wide, 
<quantity box="[346,414,230,257]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="252" unit="mm" value="2.0">2 mm</quantity>
thick in the middle, broadly obovate, cuneate at the base, apiculate at the apex, concave, glaucous to pale green, margin straight, entire, pinkish. Floral stem 1–2, erect, 11–22(–35) cm long, including the panicle, 
<quantity box="[232,319,302,329]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="5" pageNumber="252" unit="mm" value="2.5">2.5 mm</quantity>
thick in the base, pinkish green; shaft leaves 1.5–3.5 
<emphasis box="[931,950,303,328]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">×</emphasis>
<quantity box="[958,1087,302,329]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.05" metricValueMax="1.3" metricValueMin="0.8" pageId="5" pageNumber="252" unit="cm" value="1.05" valueMax="1.3" valueMin="0.8">0.8–1.3 cm</quantity>
, obovate, pinkish at the margin; panicle, 4–11 flowers, usually two branched, (1–)3–5(–6) flowers per branch (
<figureCitation box="[1020,1127,338,364]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[136,229,2032,2054]" captionTargetBox="[186,1400,436,2022]" captionTargetId="figure-158@2.[186,1400,436,2022]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Echeveria cerrograndensis. Habit variability. Photographs A and B by Gregorio Nieves; C by Rodolfo Sánchez; D by Antonio Vázquez." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5142631" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5142631/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">Figures 2</figureCitation>
&amp; 
<figureCitation box="[1165,1182,338,364]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="4.[136,229,1929,1951]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,190,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-32@4.[151,1435,190,1904]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 4. Echeveria cerrograndensis.A–B. Flower variability.C. Dissected flower showing corolla, one sepal, pistils, stamens and dark red nectaries at the base of the ovary. D–F. Panicle variability. Photographs A–D and F by Antonio Vázquez; E by Gregorio Nieves." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5142635" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5142635/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">4</figureCitation>
); pedicels straight 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" metricValueMax="1.6" metricValueMin="0.8" pageId="5" pageNumber="252" unit="mm" value="12.0" valueMax="16.0" valueMin="8.0">8–16 mm</quantity>
long; bracteoles lanceolate, 0.5–1.3 
<emphasis box="[594,613,375,400]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">×</emphasis>
<quantity box="[620,749,374,401]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="252" unit="cm" value="0.35" valueMax="0.5" valueMin="0.2">0.2–0.5 cm</quantity>
, green to with age; sepals subequal, lanceolate, straight, 0.8 
<emphasis box="[1432,1451,375,400]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">×</emphasis>
<quantity box="[136,218,410,437]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="252" unit="cm" value="0.3">0.3 cm</quantity>
; corolla urceolate pentagonal at the base, 1.2 
<emphasis box="[743,762,411,436]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">×</emphasis>
<quantity box="[771,853,410,437]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="5" pageNumber="252" unit="cm" value="1.1">1.1 cm</quantity>
; petals 5, 1.2 
<emphasis box="[1014,1033,411,436]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">×</emphasis>
<quantity box="[1042,1123,410,437]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="252" unit="cm" value="0.5">0.5 cm</quantity>
, ovate, concave, acute at the apex, pink throughout, darkened at the tip with age; pinkish white inside; nectaries renniform, dark red 0.2 
<emphasis box="[1341,1360,447,472]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">×</emphasis>
<quantity box="[1367,1447,446,473]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="252" unit="cm" value="0.1">0.1 cm</quantity>
; stamens with white filaments, 5 epipetals 0.9 x 
<quantity box="[674,751,482,509]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="252" unit="cm" value="0.1">0.1 cm</quantity>
and 5 antisepals, 1 
<emphasis box="[976,995,483,508]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">×</emphasis>
<quantity box="[1002,1083,482,509]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="252" unit="cm" value="0.1">0.1 cm</quantity>
; thecae dark red before opening, 
<quantity box="[136,212,518,545]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="252" unit="cm" value="0.2">0.2 cm</quantity>
long; ginoecium 1.1 
<emphasis box="[451,470,519,544]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">×</emphasis>
<quantity box="[476,555,518,545]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="252" unit="cm" value="0.6">0.6 cm</quantity>
, white at the base; pistils 1.1 
<emphasis box="[884,903,519,544]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="252">×</emphasis>
<quantity box="[910,988,518,545]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="252" unit="cm" value="0.3">0.3 cm</quantity>
, pinkish white at the base and red to dark red toward the apex; stigma black (
